From d57a7eeaace810a59384c1bed65d8860ec57b9b1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yaguang Tang <heut2008@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 09:22:07 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] libvirt: enable Hyper-V evmcs on Intel VMX hosts

Enable the Hyper-V eVMCS enlightenment for Windows guests only
when the hw_hyperv_evmcs image property requests it.

When requested, the scheduler requires HW_CPU_X86_INTEL_VMX,
so Placement limits builds and migrations to compatible Intel VMX
compute hosts. The libvirt driver then enables eVMCS as requested,
letting libvirt fail a forced placement to an incompatible host
instead of silently disabling it.

Add unit coverage for the opt-in behavior and scheduler trait
request, and document the image property.

Signed-off-by: Yaguang Tang <heut2008@gmail.com>
Change-Id: I60da4e6883b711126026fc73aa15c0d7354fb306
